m.blog.csdn.net/weixin_43097543/article/details/158008154\"},{\"title\":\"AI Programming Fuels Remarkable Comeback After 50% Staff Layoff\",\"url\":\"https://eu.36kr.com/en/p/3641937025322624\"},{\"title\":\"看过等于懂——2025年收尾，必看的AI“装X”指南！\",\"url\":\"https://view.inews.qq.com/wxn/20251231A05TUA00?pushid=2018052100&reJumped=1\"}]\n\nBased on my web search results, here are the key findings about new AI coding tools launched in **February 2025** that were discussed on Hacker News:\n\n## **Claude Code** - Major Launch (February 24, 2025)\n\nThe most significant AI coding tool launched in February 2025 was **Claude Code** by Anthropic:\n\n### Key Details:\n- **Launch Date**: February 24, 2025\n- **Developer**: Anthropic\n- **Type**: Terminal-based \"agentic coding\" tool\n\n### What Made It Notable:\n- Released quietly as the 2nd item in the Claude 3.7 Sonnet announcement\n- Represented a breakthrough in **agentic programming** - AI systems that can write code, execute it, check results, and iterate autonomously\n- Command-line interface that runs directly in the terminal\n- Capable of understanding entire codebases, making cross-file edits, and executing shell/git/terminal commands with user authorization\n- By July 2025, it had been used by 115,000 developers and processed 195 million lines of code per week\n\n### Hacker News Discussion:\nClaude Code was widely discussed on Hacker News throughout 2025, with threads covering:\n- Debugging low-level cryptography code\n- User experiences and best practices\n- Controversy around usage limit changes\n- Technical capabilities and comparisons to other tools\n\n---\n\n## Other Notable Mentions from February 2025:\n\n1. **Vibe Coding** - While not a tool launch itself, this concept was popularized by Andrej Karpathy in February 2025, describing a new paradigm of AI-assisted development.\n\n2. **Grok-3** - Released in February 2025 as a frontier model, mentioned in AI coding contexts.\n\nThe search results consistently point to **Claude Code** as the primary new AI coding tool launch from February 2025 that gained significant attention on Hacker News and throughout the developer community.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
